    "V ui and V ci are CKM matrix elements.• Couplings of right-handed down quarks to Z ′:∆ sd R = g Z ′ e iϕ K s12 (ϵ 1 -ϵ 2),(23)∆ bd R = g Z ′ e iϕ d s13 (2ϵ 1 + ϵ 2),(24)∆ bs R = g Z ′ e iϕs s23 (ϵ 1 + 2ϵ 2),(25)∆ ii R = g Z ′ [- 1 3 + ϵ i].",
    "(26)The real numbers s12, s13, s23 and the phases ϕ K, ϕ d, ϕ s appear in the parametrization of the rotation matrices [1].",
    "(s 12, ϕ K) only enter in the kaon sector, (s 13, ϕ d) only in the B d sector, (s 23, ϕ s) only in the B s sector.• Couplings of up-type quarks to Z ′:∆ ii L = g Z ′ [ 1 6 + ϵ i], ∆ ii R = g Z ′ [ 2 3 + ϵ i], (i = u, c, t).",
    "(27)• Couplings of left-handed charged leptons to Z ′:∆ ij L = g Z ′ [(2ϵ 1 + ϵ 2)U i1 U * j1 + (ϵ 1 + 2ϵ 2)U i2 U * j2] (i ̸ = j),(28)∆ ii L = g Z ′ [- 1 2 + (2ϵ 1 + ϵ 2)|U i1 | 2 + (ϵ 1 + 2ϵ 2)|U i2 | 2 -ϵ 1 -ϵ 2],(29)where i = e, µ, τ, and U ij are elements of the PMNS matrix.",
